---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout title="Disclaimer — Image Tools" description="What Image Tools is and isn't.">
  <header class="spine page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Image Tools</a> / <a href="/legal/">Legal</a> / Disclaimer</p>
    <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </header>

  <article class="spine prose">
    <p>
      Everything on image.oriz.in is published in good faith for general information
      only. Use it at your own risk.
    </p>

    <h2>Tool output</h2>
    <p>
      Image processing tools (compression, conversion, resizing, background
      removal, face detection) run on your device and may produce imperfect
      results depending on input format, browser, and image content. Always
      keep originals before relying on processed output.
    </p>

    <h2>Not financial advice</h2>
    <p>
      Anything written elsewhere on the oriz family related to finance is not
      investment, tax, or insurance advice.
    </p>

    <h2>Not medical advice</h2>
    <p>
      Anything related to health is for general awareness. It is not a substitute
      for consultation with a registered medical practitioner.
    </p>

    <h2>Not legal advice</h2>
    <p>
      Articles touching on tax, regulation, or compliance reflect the author's
      reading of the rules at the time of writing. Rules change. Verify with
      your own counsel before acting.
    </p>

    <h2>External links</h2>
    <p>
      We link to third-party sites we find useful. We don't control their
      content, and inclusion is not an endorsement.
    </p>

    <h2>Affiliate disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      Where applicable, oriz may earn a referral fee when you sign up to a
      service via certain links. This never affects what we recommend, and any
      such links will be marked.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

